<figureCitation id="7DF685F1FFEB5D7C8FBEFCC6FC45FCD7" box="[982,999,852,878]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,245,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,187,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[225,1362,187,1858]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aspidistra magnifica N.S.Lý, K.S.Nguyen &amp; T.S.Hoang. A. Flattened plant in flower; B. Portion of the basal part and rhizome of plant showing flower, fruit and fresh cataphyll; C. A Flower with peduncle; D. Longitudinal section of the flower (pistil removed); E. Scales; F. Flower in top view; G. Flower in bottom view; H. Basal half of the perigone with stamens; I. Pistil in top view; J. Pistil in bottom view; K. Fruit on its peduncle, and seed. Photos A–G and I–K taken from the living plant of the holotype Lý-807 (Photo by Ngọc-Sâm Lý); H from specimen SƠn, Nhân, Hồng 354 (Photo by Thanh-SƠn Hoàng)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414131" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414131/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">2</figureCitation>
