<paragraph id="E5729974FFEB5D7C8CE0FCEEFBABFC0F" blockId="1.[136,1452,892,1022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEB5D7C8C84FCEEFE26FC28" box="[236,388,892,913]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maguanensis">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEB5D7C8C84FCEEFE26FC28" box="[236,388,892,913]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">A. maguanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by its somewhat elliptic leaf blades, short flowering peduncles, much larger broadly campanulate to bowl shaped perigone tube, longer outcurved perigone lobes and larger rounded stigma.
</paragraph>
