<paragraph id="E5729974FFEE5D798CD5FC24FBDAFAAD" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D798CD5FC24FE31FC69" bold="true" box="[189,403,950,976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Similar species:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEE5D798DFCFC24FDDFFC69" box="[404,637,950,976]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D798DFCFC24FDDFFC69" box="[404,637,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Aspidistra magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEE5D798F22FC25FBC1FC68" authority="He &amp; Lv" authorityName="He &amp; Lv" box="[842,1123,950,977]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maguanensis">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D798F22FC25FC58FC69" box="[842,1018,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">A. maguanensis</emphasis>
He &amp; Lv
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="815CE485FFEE5D7988EDFC25FACCFC69" author="Xu, W. F. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; He, S. Z." box="[1157,1390,950,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" pagination="147 - 149" refId="ref4932" refString="Xu, W. F., LV, D. H., Wang, B. &amp; He, S. Z. (2017) Aspidistra maguanensis (Asparagaceae), a new species from Yunnan, China. Phytotaxa 321 (1): 147 - 149. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 312.1.16" type="journal article" year="2017">
Xu 
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D7988C6FC25FB44FC69" box="[1198,1254,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2017: 147)
</bibRefCitation>
from Gulinqing town, Maguan county, 
<collectingRegion id="27095796FFEE5D798E69FC49FDF8FC4C" box="[513,602,987,1013]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="9DDAD9E4FFEE5D798E0DFC48FD09FC4D" box="[613,683,986,1012]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">China</collectingCountry>
, in having purple-black flowers, twelve perigone lobes and stamens, lobes with four keels, table-shaped pistil. It differs by leaf blades 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798F12FC6CFC5BFBA0" box="[890,1017,1022,1049]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="2.15" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="0.8">0.8–3.5 cm</quantity>
apart, elliptic to oblanceolate-elliptic, short flowering peduncles 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798DD8FBB0FD8EFB84" box="[432,556,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="5.8">5.8–7.2 cm</quantity>
long, much larger campanulate to bowl-shaped perigone tube 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D79888AFBB0FAE8FB84" box="[1250,1354,1058,1085]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.0">4–4.5 cm</quantity>
in diam. at mouth (
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798C90FBD4FEC2FBD8" box="[248,352,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.0">3–3.5 cm</quantity>
at base), larger and out-curved perigone lobes (1.6–)1.8–2.2 × 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D79887EFBD4FBDDFBD8" box="[1046,1151,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.0">1–1.3 cm</quantity>
, larger and rounded stigma 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798CE0FBF8FEA5FB3C" box="[136,263,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.6 cm</quantity>
in diam., adaxially flattened at the centre and rough at the distal half. 
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEE5D79885EFBF8FAE7FB3D" box="[1078,1349,1130,1156]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maguanensis">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D79885EFBF8FAE7FB3D" box="[1078,1349,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Aspidistra maguanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from the new species by the leaves close to each other, and with oblong blades and longer petioles (
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D7989E8FB1CFF6FFB74" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="67.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="60.0">60– 75 cm</quantity>
long), longer flowering peduncles 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798E3FFB20FD65FB74" box="[599,711,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12 cm</quantity>
long, smaller cupulate perigone tube, ca. 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D7988F4FB20FB4AFB74" box="[1180,1256,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in diam., smaller and erect or slightly outcurved perigone lobes 1–1.2 × ca. 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798F66FB44FCFEFB48" box="[782,860,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="0.7">0.7 cm</quantity>
, smaller and rounded-hexangular stigma, 
<quantity id="22353491FFEE5D798947FB44FA09FB48" box="[1327,1451,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8 cm</quantity>
in diam. A detailed comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEE5D798E63FB69FD38FAAD" box="[523,666,1274,1301]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D798E63FB69FD38FAAD" box="[523,666,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">A. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="22CDE2F7FFEE5D798ED5FB69FCCDFAAD" box="[701,879,1275,1301]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maguanensis">
<emphasis id="D7B94566FFEE5D798ED5FB69FCCDFAAD" box="[701,879,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="26">A. maguanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is presented in 
<tableCitation id="A84FACCFFFEE5D798876FB68FBD0FAAD" box="[1054,1138,1274,1300]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,1348,1372]" captionText="TABLE 1. A detailed comparison of Aspidistra magnifica and A. maguanensis." pageId="4" pageNumber="26">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
